<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-10-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-10-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="144" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d144">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Stevens</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 8.]</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-10-15"><hi rend="italic">October 15,
                                        1890</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 3 of the 25th
                                ultimo, informing me that the majority report of the committee on
                                the bill in the Hawaiian Legislature to convene delegates to frame a
                                new constitution is opposed to such a convention, and stating, also,
                                that His Majesty is believed to be now opposed to such a
                                convention.</p>
                            <p>I am, sir, etc.,</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">James G.
                                Blaine.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>